{
  "texts": [
    "The Inception Score uses a pre-trained Inception model trained using RGB lung nodules.",
    "The Good-generated images should contain easily recognizable lung nodules.",
    "For each image, the Inception model should output a high probability for one class and a low probability for others.",
    "The set of all generated images should cover various nodule types.",
    "The Inception Score is calculated using these probabilities to compute the KL divergence between the conditional label distribution for each image and the marginal label distribution over the entire set of generated images."
  ]
}